WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:04.000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:01:49.960 --> 00:01:54.760
Some Justice

3
00:01:58.260 --> 00:02:00.270
"Our nightmares are over"...?

4
00:02:00.640 --> 00:02:01.730
Are you kidding?!

5
00:02:02.270 --> 00:02:04.400
You can't just write it off
as a nightmare!

6
00:02:04.850 --> 00:02:08.570
That's right! We saw the king attack
Nanohana with our own eyes!

7
00:02:08.570 --> 00:02:12.110
Yeah! The Royal Army
even shot Koza!

8
00:02:12.110 --> 00:02:15.910
How do you explain
all the bad things they've done?!

9
00:02:16.450 --> 00:02:20.120
That's not good enough
for our fallen comrades!

10
00:02:20.120 --> 00:02:21.950
Yeah! That's right!

11
00:02:23.870 --> 00:02:26.960
Drop your weapons, Royal Army!

12
00:02:31.710 --> 00:02:32.970
Commander Chaka!

13
00:02:34.880 --> 00:02:36.390
Chaka...

14
00:02:37.050 --> 00:02:39.060
Hey, what's going on?

15
00:02:39.060 --> 00:02:40.060
You...

16
00:02:44.270 --> 00:02:47.310
You too, Rebel Army!

17
00:02:49.610 --> 00:02:51.530
I-Igaram!

18
00:02:51.530 --> 00:02:53.150
Commander!

19
00:03:00.490 --> 00:03:01.950
Igaram...

20
00:03:07.580 --> 00:03:09.210
Igaram...

21
00:03:12.960 --> 00:03:16.550
Let us meet safely in our motherland.

22
00:03:19.760 --> 00:03:23.140
It's that old pervert
from Whisky Peak!

23
00:03:23.140 --> 00:03:24.270
He survived!

24
00:03:24.270 --> 00:03:25.600
Um, who's that?

25
00:03:28.020 --> 00:03:29.980
Hello? Can you speak?

26
00:03:31.270 --> 00:03:32.020
Yes...

27
00:03:32.020 --> 00:03:34.280
That's the boy from Nanohana...

28
00:03:34.280 --> 00:03:36.820
That's right... The one who
the Royal Army attacked.

29
00:03:37.240 --> 00:03:39.240
No, you're wrong...

30
00:03:39.240 --> 00:03:42.740
They weren't the ones who hurt me...

31
00:03:42.740 --> 00:03:45.120
Everyone, listen! I saw it!

32
00:03:47.540 --> 00:03:50.960
I just can't feel relaxed
without this on!

33
00:03:54.590 --> 00:03:56.010
Iffy!

34
00:03:59.680 --> 00:04:00.970
He's right...

35
00:04:01.550 --> 00:04:05.270
This battle was a trap
from the beginning...

36
00:04:07.060 --> 00:04:08.100
Koza!

37
00:04:08.100 --> 00:04:09.150
Leader!

38
00:04:10.310 --> 00:04:13.480
I will explain everything...

39
00:04:13.980 --> 00:04:16.490
that happened to this country.

40
00:04:17.490 --> 00:04:19.450
Everyone, drop your weapons!

41
00:04:34.380 --> 00:04:35.510
Princess Vivi!

42
00:04:38.260 --> 00:04:39.550
Where...

43
00:04:40.010 --> 00:04:41.340
is everyone?

44
00:04:42.090 --> 00:04:44.720
Hey, walk steady.

45
00:04:45.470 --> 00:04:49.140
Well, listen... I'm coming down with
the if-I-walk-more-I'll-die disease...

46
00:04:49.140 --> 00:04:50.270
Then stay there.

47
00:04:50.270 --> 00:04:53.610
What?! Well, w-wait!
Whoa! Hey! Hey! Hey!

48
00:04:53.610 --> 00:04:55.610
Hey! Hey! Why're you
pulling me by my foot?!

49
00:04:55.610 --> 00:04:56.230
Huh?

50
00:04:56.230 --> 00:04:57.070
Found him?

51
00:05:02.030 --> 00:05:03.160
Who are you?

52
00:05:04.160 --> 00:05:08.410
Thanks for carrying
that guy on your back.

53
00:05:08.410 --> 00:05:09.660
He's one of ours.

54
00:05:09.660 --> 00:05:10.870
I'll take him now.

55
00:05:10.870 --> 00:05:16.340
Then you are the pirates who
returned Vivi to this country?

56
00:05:17.590 --> 00:05:18.840
Who are you?

57
00:05:18.840 --> 00:05:19.840
Daddy!

58
00:05:20.550 --> 00:05:21.800
Everyone!

59
00:05:22.470 --> 00:05:24.140
Oh, it's Vivi!

60
00:05:25.140 --> 00:05:26.180
"Daddy"?

61
00:05:27.470 --> 00:05:29.600
Vivi's father?!

62
00:05:30.100 --> 00:05:31.770
Are you the king?

63
00:05:32.100 --> 00:05:37.150
I was prepared to die,
but he saved me.

64
00:05:37.650 --> 00:05:40.820
Exhausted after
his battle with Crocodile,

65
00:05:40.820 --> 00:05:44.370
he carried two people
and rushed to the surface...

66
00:05:44.370 --> 00:05:47.410
His strength is unbelievable...

67
00:05:47.410 --> 00:05:51.540
So we don't need to worry
about the venom?

68
00:05:51.540 --> 00:05:52.620
Correct.

69
00:05:52.620 --> 00:05:54.250
It should be neutralized by now.

70
00:05:54.250 --> 00:05:57.750
But he needs medical attention...

71
00:05:57.750 --> 00:05:58.710
You all do.

72
00:06:01.970 --> 00:06:03.970
More importantly,
Vivi, get a move on.

73
00:06:03.970 --> 00:06:04.720
What?

74
00:06:04.720 --> 00:06:06.430
Go back to the square.

75
00:06:07.560 --> 00:06:08.640
He's right!

76
00:06:08.640 --> 00:06:11.060
The Rebellion is finally over.

77
00:06:11.060 --> 00:06:14.440
It wouldn't be right if the royal
family didn't say anything.

78
00:06:14.940 --> 00:06:16.810
Right... I'll be sure
to mention all of y–

79
00:06:16.810 --> 00:06:17.940
Vivi.

80
00:06:18.520 --> 00:06:19.780
You know how it is...

81
00:06:21.690 --> 00:06:23.780
We're at large.

82
00:06:24.660 --> 00:06:27.160
We can't get mixed up
in some country's business.

83
00:06:27.530 --> 00:06:29.540
I'm hungry.

84
00:06:29.540 --> 00:06:32.040
We're going on ahead to the palace.

85
00:06:32.040 --> 00:06:33.250
I'm exhausted.

86
00:06:53.520 --> 00:06:54.310
Okay.

87
00:06:54.310 --> 00:06:56.940
Understood, Captain Smoker.

88
00:06:57.480 --> 00:06:59.900
So it was Sir Crocodile?

89
00:07:00.440 --> 00:07:02.860
He was behind everything...?

90
00:07:02.860 --> 00:07:04.200
Oh my...

91
00:07:04.200 --> 00:07:05.400
I can't believe it...

92
00:07:05.910 --> 00:07:07.370
Hey, look!

93
00:07:07.820 --> 00:07:08.990
It's the Marines!

94
00:07:15.120 --> 00:07:18.290
A rainmaking ship
owned by Baroque Works

95
00:07:18.290 --> 00:07:20.920
containing dance powder
has been discovered.

96
00:07:22.590 --> 00:07:25.970
The president of secret crime
syndicate Baroque Works

97
00:07:25.970 --> 00:07:29.300
and Warlord of the Sea,
Sir Crocodile...

98
00:07:33.980 --> 00:07:35.890
Where did that damn croc go?!

99
00:07:39.190 --> 00:07:40.480
is henceforth...

100
00:07:40.480 --> 00:07:42.860
stripped of all titles and rights,

101
00:07:42.860 --> 00:07:46.110
including his license
to capture enemy ships,

102
00:07:46.110 --> 00:07:50.740
by Marine Headquarters, an entity
under the World Government.

103
00:08:12.850 --> 00:08:14.100
Just you wait...

104
00:08:22.190 --> 00:08:26.570
We'll never be able to atone
for what we've done.

105
00:08:26.940 --> 00:08:28.150
Leader...

106
00:08:28.740 --> 00:08:32.160
I don't know what to say
to everyone...

107
00:08:33.490 --> 00:08:35.830
It is natural to regret.

108
00:08:35.830 --> 00:08:38.580
It is also natural to feel overwhelmed.

109
00:08:40.250 --> 00:08:41.500
King Cobra!

110
00:08:41.500 --> 00:08:42.960
Your Majesty...

111
00:08:43.290 --> 00:08:45.920
We have lost so much...

112
00:08:46.260 --> 00:08:48.380
and have gained nothing in return...

113
00:08:50.890 --> 00:08:53.430
However, this is a step forward!

114
00:08:53.850 --> 00:08:56.100
No matter which side you fought for,

115
00:08:56.100 --> 00:08:59.440
the battle has come and gone.

116
00:09:03.400 --> 00:09:04.730
Your Majesty...

117
00:09:05.610 --> 00:09:10.030
No one can undo the past.

118
00:09:13.700 --> 00:09:17.660
We must move past this war, and live!

119
00:09:27.340 --> 00:09:28.630
He truly has no equal...

120
00:09:32.590 --> 00:09:35.810
Long live the Kingdom of Alabasta!

121
00:09:38.890 --> 00:09:42.350
The battle that will be
engraved in history...

122
00:09:55.570 --> 00:09:56.950
and...

123
00:09:57.490 --> 00:10:00.120
the battle that will never be known...

124
00:10:02.710 --> 00:10:04.460
has finally ended...

125
00:10:06.960 --> 00:10:12.050
North Coast
Kingdom of Alabasta

126
00:10:08.420 --> 00:10:10.050
Smoker!

127
00:10:10.050 --> 00:10:12.050
What is this rain?

128
00:10:12.050 --> 00:10:15.640
Don't tell me you used the dance powder?

129
00:10:16.640 --> 00:10:17.970
Don't be stupid.

130
00:10:18.890 --> 00:10:21.520
I know better than to commit a crime.

131
00:10:22.270 --> 00:10:27.270
The king of Alabasta
never used the powder.

132
00:10:27.270 --> 00:10:29.280
What's the point in me
ruining that now?

133
00:10:30.320 --> 00:10:31.610
Oh, excuse me.

134
00:10:31.610 --> 00:10:32.990
Hina's sorry.

135
00:10:34.110 --> 00:10:38.200
But I can't believe the White Hound
of all men would be so sweet.

136
00:10:38.200 --> 00:10:41.450
Maybe you're going soft...

137
00:10:41.450 --> 00:10:42.790
Mind your own business.

138
00:10:42.830 --> 00:10:47.880
Captain "Black Cage" Hina
Marine Headquarters

139
00:10:43.620 --> 00:10:45.620
At any rate, you've got some nerve...

140
00:10:46.210 --> 00:10:50.300
using my elite unit just to look for a ship.

141
00:10:50.300 --> 00:10:51.710
This is very upsetting...

142
00:10:52.880 --> 00:10:54.680
Hina's upset!

143
00:10:54.680 --> 00:10:56.800
Come on, we both joined
in the same year.

144
00:10:56.800 --> 00:10:57.930
Cut me some slack.

145
00:10:57.930 --> 00:10:59.310
You always say that.

146
00:10:59.310 --> 00:11:01.930
Poor Tashigi. Always
cleaning up your messes.

147
00:11:03.890 --> 00:11:05.020
More importantly...

148
00:11:06.600 --> 00:11:08.980
bring in this rainmaking ship.

149
00:11:08.980 --> 00:11:09.820
Why?

150
00:11:10.400 --> 00:11:11.730
And also...

151
00:11:11.730 --> 00:11:14.030
Tashigi's on her way here
with Crocodile.

152
00:11:14.030 --> 00:11:15.780
Bring him in, too.

153
00:11:15.780 --> 00:11:17.530
Give me a break!

154
00:11:15.820 --> 00:11:20.280
Downpour
The Rainmaking Ship
Baroque Works

155
00:11:17.530 --> 00:11:19.660
Why are you so selfish?

156
00:11:23.910 --> 00:11:24.790
Heads!

157
00:11:26.830 --> 00:11:27.830
It's tails.

158
00:11:27.830 --> 00:11:29.920
You lose.

159
00:11:31.250 --> 00:11:33.630
You really are selfish,
you know that?!

160
00:11:33.630 --> 00:11:36.880
Always like this,
even when we were rookies.

161
00:11:36.880 --> 00:11:38.430
Hina's disappointed.

162
00:11:38.430 --> 00:11:40.390
That's fine.

163
00:11:40.390 --> 00:11:41.350
I'm well aware.

164
00:11:46.600 --> 00:11:49.060
That's... an order.

165
00:11:49.060 --> 00:11:50.560
Sergeant Major!

166
00:11:50.560 --> 00:11:52.360
This is a once-in-a-lifetime chance!

167
00:11:52.690 --> 00:11:56.070
When they wake up,
we won't be able t–

168
00:11:56.070 --> 00:11:57.570
I...

169
00:11:57.570 --> 00:12:01.030
forbid you to lay a hand on them!

170
00:12:01.450 --> 00:12:02.950
Wh-Why?!

171
00:12:02.950 --> 00:12:06.330
They're all sitting ducks!

172
00:12:07.960 --> 00:12:09.210
Leader...

173
00:12:09.210 --> 00:12:11.340
How bad are your injuries?

174
00:12:12.800 --> 00:12:14.420
Please don't die...

175
00:12:14.420 --> 00:12:17.010
You see, Uncle Toto was...
Yuba was...

176
00:12:17.340 --> 00:12:18.680
Vivi...

177
00:12:18.680 --> 00:12:21.510
Looks like you're
the same old worrywart...

178
00:12:21.510 --> 00:12:22.890
I don't know about Yuba,

179
00:12:22.890 --> 00:12:26.980
but my old man's definitely
too damn stubborn to die.

180
00:12:27.480 --> 00:12:28.520
Leader...

181
00:12:28.520 --> 00:12:31.940
And I've got his blood in my veins.

182
00:12:32.310 --> 00:12:34.940
As soon as I get treated,
I'm heading to Yuba.

183
00:12:35.320 --> 00:12:37.190
Don't worry...

184
00:12:37.190 --> 00:12:38.990
I'll keep in touch.

185
00:12:40.700 --> 00:12:41.450
Okay...

186
00:12:42.910 --> 00:12:44.950
It's raining!

187
00:12:44.950 --> 00:12:47.830
Rain! It's raining for
the first time in three years!

188
00:12:47.830 --> 00:12:49.830
This rain will end the Rebellion!

189
00:12:49.830 --> 00:12:52.040
Our foolish sons will come home!

190
00:12:54.040 --> 00:12:55.630
It's raining!

191
00:13:10.270 --> 00:13:13.150
Just how long are you gonna
stay so stubborn, old man?!

192
00:13:13.560 --> 00:13:15.400
Yuba is done for.

193
00:13:15.400 --> 00:13:19.070
What are you gonna do
here by yourself?!

194
00:13:19.490 --> 00:13:21.660
Do you plan on dying with the city?!

195
00:13:21.660 --> 00:13:23.740
Old man!

196
00:13:26.330 --> 00:13:27.830
Look...

197
00:13:27.830 --> 00:13:28.540
Koza.

198
00:13:29.540 --> 00:13:31.210
The rains have come.

199
00:13:32.790 --> 00:13:35.710
Just three years...

200
00:13:36.300 --> 00:13:39.210
That's all it took.

201
00:13:41.840 --> 00:13:43.260
Right...

202
00:13:44.760 --> 00:13:46.260
rain...?

203
00:13:50.140 --> 00:13:53.600
The rain now comes naturally...

204
00:13:54.730 --> 00:13:57.780
and falls endlessly within the kingdom.

205
00:14:16.500 --> 00:14:18.170
Your Highness...

206
00:14:18.170 --> 00:14:20.510
You're still awake?

207
00:14:20.510 --> 00:14:21.590
Igaram...

208
00:14:24.640 --> 00:14:26.430
Can't sleep?

209
00:14:26.430 --> 00:14:27.430
It's not that.

210
00:14:28.890 --> 00:14:30.600
I just don't want to.

211
00:14:31.850 --> 00:14:35.440
I just want to watch the rain fall.

212
00:14:52.290 --> 00:14:54.290
About Pell...

213
00:14:55.920 --> 00:14:57.290
He was...

214
00:14:57.670 --> 00:15:01.510
the noblest and strongest
warrior I've ever known.

215
00:15:02.050 --> 00:15:02.800
Yes...

216
00:15:03.800 --> 00:15:06.970
I wanted to thank him...

217
00:15:08.510 --> 00:15:09.470
He'd be...

218
00:15:10.140 --> 00:15:12.430
greatly honored by that...

219
00:15:16.980 --> 00:15:21.360
The Following Day

220
00:15:21.400 --> 00:15:27.320
Tamarisk
Alabasta's Eastern Port

221
00:15:22.900 --> 00:15:24.820
Captain Smoker, Miss Hina!

222
00:15:24.820 --> 00:15:26.780
Sergeant Major Tashigi has arrived.

223
00:15:27.740 --> 00:15:29.740
– Welcome back.
– Welcome back.

224
00:15:30.160 --> 00:15:32.410
It's been a while, Tashigi.

225
00:15:33.330 --> 00:15:34.460
Hina...

226
00:15:36.250 --> 00:15:37.460
Hello...

227
00:15:38.000 --> 00:15:42.420
I'm... a little tired,
so I'm going to lie down.

228
00:15:45.630 --> 00:15:48.890
Captain Smoker, I've returned!

229
00:15:48.890 --> 00:15:50.970
Yeah, good work out there.

230
00:15:52.010 --> 00:15:54.100
I heard about the Straw Hats.

231
00:15:54.890 --> 00:15:56.230
I'm sorry...

232
00:15:57.140 --> 00:15:58.770
I helped the pirates

233
00:15:58.770 --> 00:16:01.650
and let our opportunity
to capture them slip away.

234
00:16:03.150 --> 00:16:07.400
My actions bring nothing
but shame to the Marines.

235
00:16:07.780 --> 00:16:09.410
Why are you apologizing?

236
00:16:09.410 --> 00:16:13.160
Didn't you follow
your sense of justice?

237
00:16:14.450 --> 00:16:16.290
No... that's not it...

238
00:16:17.660 --> 00:16:18.710
Sergeant Major...

239
00:16:22.880 --> 00:16:24.510
I just...

240
00:16:25.260 --> 00:16:26.840
didn't have any other choice...

241
00:16:27.760 --> 00:16:30.550
Losers shouldn't preach about justice.

242
00:16:31.720 --> 00:16:34.060
This sea is for the mighty.

243
00:16:37.310 --> 00:16:39.020
Where did that damn croc go?!

244
00:16:40.060 --> 00:16:41.980
Tell me!

245
00:16:43.020 --> 00:16:44.980
Even when I knew
where the enemy was...

246
00:16:45.730 --> 00:16:48.030
all I could do was
tell him the location...

247
00:16:48.950 --> 00:16:50.990
Even when I knew
the time of the attack...

248
00:16:51.410 --> 00:16:53.990
all I could do was assist them...

249
00:16:54.870 --> 00:16:56.160
Justice...?

250
00:16:57.960 --> 00:17:01.120
There was none that I could follow...

251
00:17:04.800 --> 00:17:08.550
Those who you thought
were your peers

252
00:17:08.550 --> 00:17:12.090
are suddenly and rapidly
growing in notoriety.

253
00:17:14.050 --> 00:17:19.810
They know that in this sea,
they'll die if they don't rise up.

254
00:17:20.940 --> 00:17:22.690
Move forward or die?

255
00:17:23.560 --> 00:17:26.280
Whose idea was it
to come here anyway?

256
00:17:31.740 --> 00:17:32.950
Excuse me...

257
00:17:33.530 --> 00:17:34.450
but...

258
00:17:35.030 --> 00:17:36.910
I'm going to lie down for a bit.

259
00:17:49.550 --> 00:17:50.550
You idiot...

260
00:17:52.300 --> 00:17:54.640
If you're frustrated enough to cry...

261
00:17:54.640 --> 00:17:56.640
then become stronger!

262
00:18:06.440 --> 00:18:09.280
I will!

263
00:18:15.370 --> 00:18:18.910
I wish you guys had her guts.

264
00:18:19.450 --> 00:18:21.830
Now, carry them aboard!

265
00:18:21.830 --> 00:18:22.830
– Yes, sir!
– Yes, sir!

266
00:18:23.960 --> 00:18:26.460
Captain Smoker! Call from HQ!

267
00:18:27.250 --> 00:18:29.130
This is Marine Headquarters.

268
00:18:29.130 --> 00:18:31.470
Is this Captain Smoker?

269
00:18:31.470 --> 00:18:32.590
Speaking.

270
00:18:32.970 --> 00:18:35.970
The government's
top officials have decided

271
00:18:35.970 --> 00:18:38.970
to give you and
Sergeant Major Tashigi medals

272
00:18:38.970 --> 00:18:41.600
for defeating Crocodile.

273
00:18:41.600 --> 00:18:43.480
For defeating...?

274
00:18:43.480 --> 00:18:45.350
Hey, wait just a damn second!

275
00:18:45.350 --> 00:18:49.110
We're not the ones
who took down Crocodile.

276
00:18:49.110 --> 00:18:51.190
Did they even listen to our report?

277
00:18:51.190 --> 00:18:56.370
Furthermore, each of you
will be promoted by one rank, so...

278
00:18:56.370 --> 00:18:58.620
Hey! Listen up!

279
00:18:58.620 --> 00:19:04.000
The ones who've been fighting Crocodile
and his Baroque Works this whole time...

280
00:19:04.000 --> 00:19:05.750
were the Straw Hat Pirates!

281
00:19:06.210 --> 00:19:08.000
Don't bother, Smoker.

282
00:19:08.000 --> 00:19:11.460
They probably plan
to cover everything up.

283
00:19:12.010 --> 00:19:15.880
The entire government was slow
to realize the crisis in Alabasta.

284
00:19:15.880 --> 00:19:19.550
You think they can tell the world
that it was saved by pirates?

285
00:19:20.310 --> 00:19:23.730
So, we'd like both of you to attend
your award ceremony and...

286
00:19:23.730 --> 00:19:25.270
You can't be serious!

287
00:19:25.770 --> 00:19:28.150
Smoker! Just accept it!

288
00:19:28.150 --> 00:19:30.860
Who knows what'll happen
if you defy the top brass!

289
00:19:30.860 --> 00:19:33.530
We took Crocodile down?!

290
00:19:34.190 --> 00:19:37.240
My subordinate's crying
over there because we couldn't.

291
00:19:37.610 --> 00:19:38.910
Hey, you...

292
00:19:39.490 --> 00:19:42.990
Give the old geezers at the top
a message for me.

293
00:19:42.990 --> 00:19:43.500
Huh?

294
00:19:43.500 --> 00:19:44.410
Smoker!

295
00:19:44.910 --> 00:19:47.250
"Go to hell!"

296
00:19:53.130 --> 00:19:54.300
Oh...

297
00:19:54.300 --> 00:19:56.930
Your compounding is amazing!

298
00:19:56.930 --> 00:20:00.390
Though quite unusual...
Well, it is practical. Wonderful, even.

299
00:20:02.560 --> 00:20:05.560
Wherever did you learn
those medical skills?

300
00:20:05.560 --> 00:20:07.980
Tony is a doctor from Drum.

301
00:20:07.980 --> 00:20:11.730
Why, is that so? They used to be
famous for their advanced medicine...

302
00:20:13.570 --> 00:20:14.940
The rumors were true...

303
00:20:15.440 --> 00:20:17.700
I've been a doctor for forty years,

304
00:20:17.700 --> 00:20:20.450
but I did not know such
techniques could even exist.

305
00:20:21.320 --> 00:20:23.580
They are truly brilliant.

306
00:20:23.580 --> 00:20:27.370
I'm no match for you
despite your youth.

307
00:20:28.250 --> 00:20:31.170
Shut up! Quit gawking, you idiot!

308
00:20:31.170 --> 00:20:33.090
Go away, you bastard!

309
00:20:33.090 --> 00:20:37.720
Should I assume he means "feel free
to have some tea and watch"?

310
00:20:37.720 --> 00:20:39.380
I think so.

311
00:20:39.760 --> 00:20:42.350
Well... Really, you're outstanding!

312
00:20:42.350 --> 00:20:44.260
Shut up...

313
00:20:45.600 --> 00:20:48.100
I can only say I'm impressed.

314
00:20:48.100 --> 00:20:49.690
Oh boy, your skills are amazing!

315
00:20:50.060 --> 00:20:52.860
Go away! Shut up, you bastard!

316
00:20:59.910 --> 00:21:01.950
Hey! Do you have more lumber?

317
00:21:01.950 --> 00:21:03.330
I don't have enough either!

318
00:21:03.330 --> 00:21:05.450
I've got some extra. Help yourselves.

319
00:21:05.450 --> 00:21:06.910
Oh, thanks!

320
00:21:06.910 --> 00:21:08.540
This country is sturdy...

321
00:21:08.540 --> 00:21:10.670
That's because the princess is cute.

322
00:21:10.670 --> 00:21:11.540
For real?

323
00:21:11.540 --> 00:21:12.170
Yup!

324
00:21:12.170 --> 00:21:13.130
Dammit!

325
00:21:13.460 --> 00:21:15.170
Each house was busted through!

326
00:21:15.170 --> 00:21:16.340
What are these holes?!

327
00:21:16.340 --> 00:21:18.550
It looks like someone
kicked through them.

328
00:21:18.550 --> 00:21:19.800
Whoa! This is terrible.

329
00:21:19.800 --> 00:21:21.130
Hey, Usopp! Look!

330
00:21:21.130 --> 00:21:22.890
There's something over there...

331
00:21:22.890 --> 00:21:24.010
Huh?

332
00:21:28.060 --> 00:21:29.850
I must improve my concentration.

333
00:21:30.850 --> 00:21:34.020
Until I can bring out
that power at any time...

334
00:21:34.020 --> 00:21:36.570
I can't consider myself stronger.

335
00:21:36.980 --> 00:21:39.150
Whoa... You have so many
interesting books!

336
00:21:39.490 --> 00:21:41.110
Can I really have them?

337
00:21:41.110 --> 00:21:42.410
Consider them yours.

338
00:21:42.410 --> 00:21:44.120
I've already read them all.

339
00:21:44.450 --> 00:21:45.740
Thank you!

340
00:21:45.740 --> 00:21:48.330
Then I'll help myself.

341
00:21:48.830 --> 00:21:51.500
Did you not hear me?!
I don't know! Begone!

342
00:21:51.920 --> 00:21:54.130
If you lie, it'll only harm your country!

343
00:21:54.130 --> 00:21:55.880
Harboring pirates is a felony.

344
00:21:55.880 --> 00:21:56.880
– Hey.
– Hey, what's up?

345
00:21:56.880 --> 00:21:58.000
Oh, welcome back.

346
00:21:58.340 --> 00:22:01.630
I think we were able to buy enough,
considering the state of the city...

347
00:21:59.760 --> 00:22:02.470
Do you have any evidence
that pirates are here?!

348
00:22:01.630 --> 00:22:02.470
Yeah...

349
00:22:02.470 --> 00:22:04.430
W-Well, that's...

350
00:22:04.800 --> 00:22:06.350
I wonder if he's up yet...

351
00:22:06.350 --> 00:22:06.390
I wonder if he's up yet...

352
00:22:06.390 --> 00:22:06.430
I wonder if he's up yet...

353
00:22:06.430 --> 00:22:06.470
I wonder if he's up yet...

354
00:22:06.470 --> 00:22:06.510
I wonder if he's up yet...
When he wakes up,
he's gonna make a racket...

355
00:22:06.510 --> 00:22:06.560
I wonder if he's up yet...
When he wakes up,
he's gonna make a racket...

356
00:22:06.560 --> 00:22:06.600
When he wakes up,
he's gonna make a racket...

357
00:22:06.600 --> 00:22:06.640
When he wakes up,
he's gonna make a racket...

358
00:22:06.640 --> 00:22:06.680
When he wakes up,
he's gonna make a racket...

359
00:22:06.680 --> 00:22:09.390
When he wakes up,
he's gonna make a racket...

360
00:22:09.390 --> 00:22:10.930
Man...

361
00:22:10.930 --> 00:22:13.020
I slept so good!

362
00:22:15.150 --> 00:22:16.690
Oh? My hat?

363
00:22:16.690 --> 00:22:18.650
My hat! Where's my hat?!

364
00:22:18.650 --> 00:22:20.650
I'm starving! Breakfast!

365
00:22:20.650 --> 00:22:23.150
Hey, breakfast! Where's my hat?!
Breakfast! My hat?!

366
00:22:23.530 --> 00:22:26.030
You just woke up
and you're already loud!

367
00:22:26.030 --> 00:22:28.910
And it's not time for breakfast.
It's early evening.

368
00:22:28.910 --> 00:22:30.790
Your hat is over there.

369
00:22:30.790 --> 00:22:33.120
A soldier found it
in front of the palace.

370
00:22:33.790 --> 00:22:35.040
Oh, good!

371
00:22:35.040 --> 00:22:37.420
I'm so glad you're okay, Luffy!

372
00:22:37.420 --> 00:22:40.010
Okay? I've always been okay.

373
00:22:40.010 --> 00:22:43.130
You were seriously hurt, dummy!
A high fever and everything!

374
00:22:43.130 --> 00:22:46.260
Vivi and Chopper had to take care
of you this whole time!

375
00:22:46.260 --> 00:22:48.220
Really? Thanks!

376
00:22:49.010 --> 00:22:50.640
Oh hey, Luffy! You're up?

377
00:22:50.640 --> 00:22:52.770
Hey, Zoro! Long time no see!

378
00:22:52.770 --> 00:22:53.980
"Long time no see"?

379
00:22:53.980 --> 00:22:56.690
Hey! You were training
again, weren't you?!

380
00:22:56.690 --> 00:22:58.320
What? It's my business, right?

381
00:22:58.320 --> 00:23:01.570
No means no! I'm the doctor here!
And stop removing your bandages!

382
00:23:01.570 --> 00:23:03.150
It's hard to move with them.

383
00:23:03.150 --> 00:23:04.820
Then don't move!

384
00:23:04.820 --> 00:23:06.820
"Long time no see"...?

385
00:23:06.820 --> 00:23:08.030
"Long time no see"?

386
00:23:08.030 --> 00:23:11.790
No, you're not wrong... considering
you've been asleep for three days.

387
00:23:11.790 --> 00:23:14.040
Three days?! I slept
for three whole days?!

388
00:23:14.040 --> 00:23:14.790
Yep.

389
00:23:17.380 --> 00:23:19.000
I missed fifteen meals...

390
00:23:19.000 --> 00:23:21.050
So you can do quick math
if it's for food?!

391
00:23:21.050 --> 00:23:23.010
And he assumed five meals a day!

392
00:23:24.090 --> 00:23:25.720
Is the captain really awake?!

393
00:23:26.090 --> 00:23:28.800
It'll be dinnertime soon,
so could you wait a little?

394
00:23:28.800 --> 00:23:29.390
Wha...?!

395
00:23:29.390 --> 00:23:31.640
Oh, hey, tube-hair guy! You're alive?!

396
00:23:31.640 --> 00:23:33.980
S-So you really were
into that sort of thing...

397
00:23:33.980 --> 00:23:35.520
No, everyone.

398
00:23:35.520 --> 00:23:37.100
That's Terracotta.

399
00:23:37.100 --> 00:23:39.980
She's Igaram's wife and head
of the palace service staff.

400
00:23:39.980 --> 00:23:41.980
Thank you for helping our country.

401
00:23:41.980 --> 00:23:45.320
Wives can resemble their husbands,
but this is too much!

402
00:23:45.320 --> 00:23:47.320
I heard you eat a lot.

403
00:23:47.320 --> 00:23:51.280
Would you have some fruit
to hold you over until dinner?

404
00:23:50.660 --> 00:23:51.280
Okay.

405
00:23:51.870 --> 00:23:53.160
– Are you a magician?!
– Are you a magician?!

406
00:23:53.540 --> 00:23:55.330
Lady, I need three days of food!

407
00:23:55.330 --> 00:23:57.920
Splendid! I've devoted
thirty years to serving!

408
00:23:57.920 --> 00:24:01.590
I won't lose against a youngster's
stomach! Eat as much as you like!

409
00:24:07.260 --> 00:24:09.300
They don't have a shred of dignity...

410
00:24:09.300 --> 00:24:13.520
Meals in this dining hall
are meant to be stately...

411
00:24:15.230 --> 00:24:17.190
So he wasn't bluffing.
But I won't lose!

412
00:24:17.940 --> 00:24:19.650
Eat before it's gone!

413
00:24:21.270 --> 00:24:23.110
Hey, Luffy! You took
my food, didn't you?!

414
00:24:24.110 --> 00:24:25.070
Don't spit the food!

415
00:24:25.570 --> 00:24:27.740
Hey, hey, if you eat too fast, you'll...

416
00:24:27.740 --> 00:24:29.160
We've got a lot, so...

417
00:24:29.280 --> 00:24:32.870
Just you wait and see, Luffy.
I'll put a tabasco star on this.

418
00:24:36.750 --> 00:24:38.370
Hey! When did you...?!

419
00:24:39.670 --> 00:24:40.880
What's that called?

420
00:24:40.880 --> 00:24:43.590
This is kunafa. You bake
noodles in the oven and...

421
00:24:44.210 --> 00:24:45.550
Delicious!

422
00:24:45.550 --> 00:24:47.720
Now, here's more!

423
00:24:48.090 --> 00:24:50.970
Man, I diffn mow mu mere meh ming!

424
00:24:50.970 --> 00:24:54.100
Men mu're Mimi's mad, muh?

425
00:24:54.100 --> 00:24:56.270
W-Well... Let this wait
until after dinner.

426
00:24:56.270 --> 00:24:57.100
Meah, mokay.

427
00:24:58.640 --> 00:25:00.520
Can I get a refill?!

428
00:25:00.600 --> 00:25:02.110
Hey, we need some water!

429
00:25:03.360 --> 00:25:05.480
What a noisy dinner...

430
00:25:05.480 --> 00:25:07.440
I can't watch. They're too vulgar...

431
00:25:11.280 --> 00:25:14.240
How can the princess
just keep laughing...?

432
00:25:42.940 --> 00:25:45.110
This is the palace's pride,
the great bath.

433
00:25:45.110 --> 00:25:47.610
We normally only use it
during the rainy season.

434
00:25:46.780 --> 00:25:47.610
Amazing!

435
00:25:47.610 --> 00:25:48.990
This is gorgeous! Gorgeous!

436
00:25:48.990 --> 00:25:51.110
I'm going in first!

437
00:25:49.940 --> 00:25:51.110
No, I am!

438
00:25:52.110 --> 00:25:53.410
Are you guys having fun?

439
00:25:53.410 --> 00:25:56.490
Well, I really enjoyed the dinner.

440
00:25:56.490 --> 00:25:59.500
I hoped to keep it simple
due to our circumstances,

441
00:25:59.500 --> 00:26:03.370
but it seems you bunch
turn everything into a party.

442
00:26:03.750 --> 00:26:06.460
Hey, Zoro, look at this!
We can train here!

443
00:26:06.460 --> 00:26:07.380
Train! Train!

444
00:26:07.380 --> 00:26:08.340
How, exactly?

445
00:26:09.010 --> 00:26:10.970
So where's the women's bath?

446
00:26:10.970 --> 00:26:12.840
Are you crazy?!
Why would I tell you?!

447
00:26:12.840 --> 00:26:14.340
The princess is there!

448
00:26:14.340 --> 00:26:16.300
C'mon! Spill the beans!

449
00:26:16.300 --> 00:26:17.890
It is behind that wall!

450
00:26:17.890 --> 00:26:19.430
Your Majesty! How could you?!

451
00:26:19.430 --> 00:26:21.480
Hey, you're not bad at all!

452
00:26:22.350 --> 00:26:23.560
This feels great!

453
00:26:24.100 --> 00:26:26.730
I wonder if there's a ship
with a bath as big as this...

454
00:26:26.730 --> 00:26:29.690
I'm sure there is.
The sea is a vast place.

455
00:26:30.190 --> 00:26:31.690
We saw giants...

456
00:26:31.690 --> 00:26:33.070
dinosaurs...

457
00:26:33.070 --> 00:26:35.820
cherry blossoms blooming
in a winter land...

458
00:26:35.820 --> 00:26:40.160
There must be even more
we can't imagine out at sea!

459
00:26:43.580 --> 00:26:44.870
Well...

460
00:26:44.120 --> 00:26:44.870
It's my turn.

461
00:26:46.130 --> 00:26:47.290
Thank you.

462
00:26:47.290 --> 00:26:48.590
Huh?

463
00:26:48.590 --> 00:26:50.760
Hey, what are you all doing?!

464
00:26:51.090 --> 00:26:52.720
Those idiots...

465
00:26:54.300 --> 00:26:57.220
It'll be 100,000 belly
per person, okay?!

466
00:26:58.010 --> 00:26:58.680
Huh?

467
00:26:58.680 --> 00:27:01.100
Happiness Punch!

468
00:27:01.100 --> 00:27:02.100
Nami!

469
00:27:08.520 --> 00:27:10.020
You can't decide, huh...?

470
00:27:10.980 --> 00:27:14.860
We're thinking about leaving tonight.

471
00:27:14.860 --> 00:27:15.660
Really?!

472
00:27:15.660 --> 00:27:18.280
Well, we don't have a reason
to be here anymore, right?

473
00:27:18.280 --> 00:27:20.910
And I bet the Marines
are waiting for us at the port.

474
00:27:20.910 --> 00:27:22.620
Our ship will be in danger soon.

475
00:27:25.710 --> 00:27:26.540
Thank you...

476
00:27:27.040 --> 00:27:28.080
– You dirty old man...
– You dirty old man...

477
00:27:28.080 --> 00:27:29.880
Not for that!

478
00:27:32.010 --> 00:27:33.510
For this country.

479
00:27:40.850 --> 00:27:45.020
Hey, hey, should a king
really be doing that?

480
00:27:45.020 --> 00:27:47.600
This is a grave matter, Your Majesty.

481
00:27:47.600 --> 00:27:50.230
A king must never
bow his head to anyone.

482
00:27:50.730 --> 00:27:52.610
Igaram...

483
00:27:52.610 --> 00:27:56.030
A man's title comes off
with his clothes.

484
00:27:56.450 --> 00:27:58.620
But we're in the bath...

485
00:27:58.620 --> 00:28:01.330
There is no such thing
as a naked king.

486
00:28:01.330 --> 00:28:06.160
I'd like to thank you
from the bottom of my heart...

487
00:28:06.160 --> 00:28:09.000
as a father and as
a resident of this land.

488
00:28:13.250 --> 00:28:14.840
Thank you very much.

489
00:28:15.470 --> 00:28:18.300
I truly appreciate it!

490
00:28:24.520 --> 00:28:25.890
Tonight?!

491
00:28:25.890 --> 00:28:26.850
That's right.

492
00:28:26.850 --> 00:28:28.520
We're leaving?

493
00:28:28.520 --> 00:28:31.400
Well, I think it's a good idea.

494
00:28:31.400 --> 00:28:33.690
There's no reason for us
to stick around.

495
00:28:33.690 --> 00:28:36.240
Yeah... I'm also worried
about the Marines.

496
00:28:36.240 --> 00:28:38.070
Okay, then. You decide, Luffy.

497
00:28:38.070 --> 00:28:40.240
Alright! But more Alabastan food first.

498
00:28:40.240 --> 00:28:41.700
We're leaving now, you idiot!

499
00:28:41.700 --> 00:28:43.200
– Idiot!
– You don't all have to...

500
00:28:43.580 --> 00:28:45.080
What should we do, Igaram?!

501
00:28:45.080 --> 00:28:46.910
We must inform them at once.

502
00:28:46.910 --> 00:28:48.500
Yes, of course.

503
00:28:48.500 --> 00:28:49.870
But...

504
00:28:49.870 --> 00:28:51.880
this is now a major incident...

505
00:28:52.340 --> 00:28:55.000
I hope they can leave
the island safely.

506
00:28:55.000 --> 00:28:56.840
These were printed so quickly!

507
00:28:58.300 --> 00:29:01.390
Roronoa Zoro.
Bounty: 60 million belly!

508
00:29:02.510 --> 00:29:05.930
Monkey D. Luffy.
Bounty: 100 million belly!

509
00:29:06.520 --> 00:29:07.560
Igaram...

510
00:29:07.560 --> 00:29:08.850
With such high bounties,

511
00:29:08.850 --> 00:29:12.400
Marine Headquarters'
top brass will surely act.

512
00:29:12.770 --> 00:29:15.400
There is no turning back now, Luffy.

513
00:29:16.030 --> 00:29:19.530
You and your crew took down
one of the Seven Warlords!
